--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Python port (this repository)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Copyright (c) 2026 Tikhii
  License:    Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International
              (CC BY-NC 4.0)
  Repository: https://github.com/Tikhii/libquiv-aging

The Python port introduces structural changes (modular decomposition,
substitution of ode23t with scipy.integrate.solve_ivp BDF, scalar-fast
interpolation, dataclass-based parameter packs, pytest infrastructure) but
reproduces the mathematical model and aging mechanisms of the original work
without alteration to the underlying physics.

